    <div xml:id="PN263">
      <lg type="edition" style="pūṭṭuvil">
<l>peruṅkaḷiṟ ṟaṭiyiṉ ṟōṉṟu moruka</l>
<l>ṇirumpaṟai yiravala cēṟi yāyiṉ</l>
<l>ṟoḻātaṉai kaḻita lōmpumati vaḻātu</l>
<l>vaṇṭumēm paṭūumiv vaṟanilai yāṟē</l>
<l>pallāt tiraṇirai peyartarap peyartantu</l>
<l>kallā viḷaiyar nīṅka nīṅkāṉ</l>
<l>villumiḻ kaṭuṅkaṇai mūḻkak</l>
<l>kolpuṉaṟ ciṟaiyiṉ vilaṅkiyōṉ kallē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Mendicant with the big drum with one eye that appears</l>
<l>like the foot of a large elephant bull, if you were to go (1f.)</l>
<l>on this way in a state of drought where the Vaṇṭu are unfailingly pre-eminent, (3d-4)</l>
<l>beware of passing by without worshipping [it] (3a-c)</l>
<l>– the stone of the one who was an obstacle on one wing of the murderous flood (8)</l>
<l>when fierce arrows emitted by bows sank in, (7)</l>
<l>who did not leave when the untaught young men left, (6)</l>
<l>returning to return with the growing herd of many cows. (5)</l>
</lg>
    </div>
